'''Samuel Cotes''' (1734<U+2013>1818) was a younger brother of [[Francis Cotes]], [[Royal Academy|R.A.]]. He was a successful painter of [[Portrait miniature|miniature portraits]] and also worked in crayons. He died in [[Chelsea, London|Chelsea]] in 1818.

